Computational Affordance

Every physical medium has things it does “for free.”

Silicon gives

* Boolean logic
* deterministic switching
* reliability

Water gives

* diffusion
* flow
* equilibrium

Light gives

* interference
* Fourier transforms
* enormous bandwidth

Magnetics give

* persistence
* oscillation
* synchronization
* field interaction

So instead of asking

“Can we make magnets behave like transistors?”

we ask

“What computation do magnetic systems naturally perform?”

That is a much more productive research direction.

